    "docHtml": "<p>An elongated single-edged or double-edged blade longer than a dagger but shorter than a sword, the longknife extends reach without the weight of a full blade. Fighters favor it as a secondary weapon worn at the belt, drawn when a longer steel meets close quarters or a first blade breaks. Worn by soldiers and rovers alike.</p>\n",
